  "text": "Hydroxyapatite crystals (HA) crystals were synthesized, characterized [CITATION_1] , and sonicated for 5 min in sterile PBS prior to experiment. Secondary calciprotein particles (CPP) were synthesized as previously described [CITATION_2] . Briefly, 10% FBS, 3.5 mM phosphate (2.14 mM Na 2 HPO 4 , 1.36 mM NaH 2 PO 4, Sigma), 1 mM calcium (CaCl 2 , Sigma), 1%P/S, and 1%L-Glutamine where added to DMEM. This medium was stored at 37°C for 7 days to generate secondary CPP and then centrifuged at 25000×g for 2 h at 4°C. Calcium content was measured in the resuspended pellet by the QuantiChrom™ Calcium Kit.",
